shared_text:
World Health Organization (WHO)
April 2 at 12:14 AM ·

Today is World Autism Awareness Day.

1 in 160 children has an autism spectrum disorder.
Autism begins in childhood and tend to persist into adolescence and adulthood. It refers to a range of conditions characterised by some degree of:
🔴 impaired social behaviour, communication and language
🔴 a narrow range of interests and activities that are both unique to the individual and carried out repetitively.

People with autism are often subject to stigma, discrimination and human rights violations. This needs to stop!
text:
World Health Organization (WHO)
April 2 at 12:14 AM ·

Today is World Autism Awareness Day.

1 in 160 children has an autism spectrum disorder.
Autism begins in childhood and tend to persist into adolescence and adulthood. It refers to a range of conditions characterised by some degree of:
🔴 impaired social behaviour, communication and language
🔴 a narrow range of interests and activities that are both unique to the individual and carried out repetitively.

People with autism are often subject to stigma, discrimination and human rights violations. This needs to stop!

post_text: Career and Technical Education (CTE) in action!
shared_text:
Carl Sandburg College
February 24 at 5:00 PM ·

"It's really boosted my confidence. I was nervous coming into a class with all guys. There are explosives. It's dangerous. I was not confident in myself, and to realize that I am capable of welding and basically being one of the guys...it means a lot." - Annika Spring, Galesburg High School Senior.

Annika has been busy in the Galesburg Area Vocational Center (GAVC) program, having taken classes in culinary, health occupations, and most recently welding. As a part of #CTEMonth at Sandburg, we visited with Annika to discuss her experiences in the welding program and what she plans to do in the future. She will graduate from GHS this spring and attend Carl Sandburg College this fall through the Galesburg Promise.
